feed.subtitle: Hello! I am a junior aerospace engineering student at the University of Florida with experience in robotics, mechatronics, computer-aided design, Python, and C++. I am a passionate learner, leader, and educator. Currently, I am the IREC Avionics Lead for Swamp Launch Student Rocketry at UF. This picture was taken shortly after planting a sweetgum tree that flew around the Moon in Artemis I. Thank you for visiting my portfolio!
